dnsResMIB.name: dnsResMIB

dnsResMIB.description: The MIB module for entities implementing the client (resolver) side of the Domain Name System (DNS) protocol.

DnsQClass.name: DnsQClass
DnsQClass.description: This data type is used to represent the QClass values which appear in Resource Records in the DNS. A 16-bit unsigned integer is used to allow room for new QClass records to be defined. Existing standard QClasses are listed in the DNS specification.

DnsQType.name: DnsQType
DnsQType.description: This data type is used to represent the QType values which appear in Resource Records in the DNS. A 16-bit unsigned integer is used to allow room for new QType records to be defined. Existing standard QTypes are listed in the DNS specification.

DnsRespCode.name: DnsRespCode
DnsRespCode.description: This data type is used to represent the DNS RCODE value in DNS response messages. Existing standard RCODE values are listed in the DNS specifications.

dnsResConfigImplementIdent.name: dnsResConfigImplementIdent
dnsResConfigImplementIdent.description: The implementation identification string for the resolver software in use on the system, for example; `RES-2.1'

dnsResConfigService.name: dnsResConfigService
dnsResConfigService.description: Kind of DNS resolution service provided: recursiveOnly(1) indicates a stub resolver. iterativeOnly(2) indicates a normal full service resolver. recursiveAndIterative(3) indicates a full-service resolver which performs a mix of recursive and iterative queries.

dnsResConfigMaxCnames.name: dnsResConfigMaxCnames
dnsResConfigMaxCnames.description: Limit on how many CNAMEs the resolver should allow before deciding that there's a CNAME loop. Zero means that resolver has no explicit CNAME limit.

dnsResConfigSbeltTable.name: dnsResConfigSbeltTable
dnsResConfigSbeltTable.description: Table of safety belt information used by the resolver when it hasn't got any better idea of where to send a query, such as when the resolver is booting or is a stub resolver.

dnsResConfigSbeltEntry.name: dnsResConfigSbeltEntry
dnsResConfigSbeltEntry.description: An entry in the resolver's Sbelt table. Rows may be created or deleted at any time by the DNS resolver and by SNMP SET requests. Whether the values changed via SNMP are saved in stable storage across `reset' operations is implementation-specific.

dnsResConfigSbeltAddr.name: dnsResConfigSbeltAddr
dnsResConfigSbeltAddr.description: The IP address of the Sbelt name server identified by this row of the table.

dnsResConfigSbeltName.name: dnsResConfigSbeltName
dnsResConfigSbeltName.description: The DNS name of a Sbelt nameserver identified by this row of the table. A zero-length string indicates that the name is not known by the resolver.

dnsResConfigSbeltRecursion.name: dnsResConfigSbeltRecursion
dnsResConfigSbeltRecursion.description: Kind of queries resolver will be sending to the name server identified in this row of the table: iterative(1) indicates that resolver will be directing iterative queries to this name server (RD bit turned off). recursive(2) indicates that resolver will be directing recursive queries to this name server (RD bit turned on). recursiveAndIterative(3) indicates that the resolver will be directing both recursive and iterative queries to the server identified in this row of the table.

dnsResConfigSbeltPref.name: dnsResConfigSbeltPref
dnsResConfigSbeltPref.description: This value identifies the preference for the name server identified in this row of the table. The lower the value, the more desirable the resolver considers this server.

dnsResConfigSbeltSubTree.name: dnsResConfigSbeltSubTree
dnsResConfigSbeltSubTree.description: Queries sent to the name server identified by this row of the table are limited to those for names in the name subtree identified by this variable. If no such limitation applies, the value of this variable is the name of the root domain (a DNS name consisting of a single zero octet).

dnsResConfigSbeltClass.name: dnsResConfigSbeltClass
dnsResConfigSbeltClass.description: The class of DNS queries that will be sent to the server identified by this row of the table.

dnsResConfigSbeltStatus.name: dnsResConfigSbeltStatus
dnsResConfigSbeltStatus.description: Row status column for this row of the Sbelt table.

dnsResConfigUpTime.name: dnsResConfigUpTime
dnsResConfigUpTime.description: If the resolver has a persistent state (e.g., a process), this value will be the time elapsed since it started. For software without persistant state, this value will be 0.

dnsResConfigResetTime.name: dnsResConfigResetTime
dnsResConfigResetTime.description: If the resolver has a persistent state (e.g., a process) and supports a `reset' operation (e.g., can be told to re-read configuration files), this value will be the time elapsed since the last time the resolver was `reset.' For software that does not have persistence or does not support a `reset' operation, this value will be zero.

dnsResConfigReset.name: dnsResConfigReset
dnsResConfigReset.description: Status/action object to reinitialize any persistant resolver state. When set to reset(2), any persistant resolver state (such as a process) is reinitialized as if the resolver had just been started. This value will never be returned by a read operation. When read, one of the following values will be returned: other(1) - resolver in some unknown state; initializing(3) - resolver (re)initializing; running(4) - resolver currently running.

dnsResCounterByOpcodeTable.name: dnsResCounterByOpcodeTable
dnsResCounterByOpcodeTable.description: Table of the current count of resolver queries and answers.

dnsResCounterByOpcodeEntry.name: dnsResCounterByOpcodeEntry
dnsResCounterByOpcodeEntry.description: Entry in the resolver counter table. Entries are indexed by DNS OpCode.

dnsResCounterByOpcodeCode.name: dnsResCounterByOpcodeCode
dnsResCounterByOpcodeCode.description: The index to this table. The OpCodes that have already been defined are found in RFC-1035.

dnsResCounterByOpcodeQueries.name: dnsResCounterByOpcodeQueries
dnsResCounterByOpcodeQueries.description: Total number of queries that have sent out by the resolver since initialization for the OpCode which is the index to this row of the table.

dnsResCounterByOpcodeResponses.name: dnsResCounterByOpcodeResponses
dnsResCounterByOpcodeResponses.description: Total number of responses that have been received by the resolver since initialization for the OpCode which is the index to this row of the table.

dnsResCounterByRcodeTable.name: dnsResCounterByRcodeTable
dnsResCounterByRcodeTable.description: Table of the current count of responses to resolver queries.

dnsResCounterByRcodeEntry.name: dnsResCounterByRcodeEntry
dnsResCounterByRcodeEntry.description: Entry in the resolver response table. Entries are indexed by DNS response code.

dnsResCounterByRcodeCode.name: dnsResCounterByRcodeCode
dnsResCounterByRcodeCode.description: The index to this table. The Response Codes that have already been defined are found in RFC-1035.

dnsResCounterByRcodeResponses.name: dnsResCounterByRcodeResponses
dnsResCounterByRcodeResponses.description: Number of responses the resolver has received for the response code value which identifies this row of the table.

dnsResCounterNonAuthDataResps.name: dnsResCounterNonAuthDataResps
dnsResCounterNonAuthDataResps.description: Number of requests made by the resolver for which a non-authoritative answer (cached data) was received.

dnsResCounterNonAuthNoDataResps.name: dnsResCounterNonAuthNoDataResps
dnsResCounterNonAuthNoDataResps.description: Number of requests made by the resolver for which a non-authoritative answer - no such data response (empty answer) was received.

dnsResCounterMartians.name: dnsResCounterMartians
dnsResCounterMartians.description: Number of responses received which were received from servers that the resolver does not think it asked.

dnsResCounterRecdResponses.name: dnsResCounterRecdResponses
dnsResCounterRecdResponses.description: Number of responses received to all queries.

dnsResCounterUnparseResps.name: dnsResCounterUnparseResps
dnsResCounterUnparseResps.description: Number of responses received which were unparseable.

dnsResCounterFallbacks.name: dnsResCounterFallbacks
dnsResCounterFallbacks.description: Number of times the resolver had to fall back to its seat belt information.

dnsResLameDelegationOverflows.name: dnsResLameDelegationOverflows
dnsResLameDelegationOverflows.description: Number of times the resolver attempted to add an entry to the Lame Delegation table but was unable to for some reason such as space constraints.

dnsResLameDelegationTable.name: dnsResLameDelegationTable
dnsResLameDelegationTable.description: Table of name servers returning lame delegations. A lame delegation has occured when a parent zone delegates authority for a child zone to a server that appears not to think that it is authoritative for the child zone in question.

dnsResLameDelegationEntry.name: dnsResLameDelegationEntry
dnsResLameDelegationEntry.description: Entry in lame delegation table. Only the resolver may create rows in this table. SNMP SET requests may be used to delete rows.

dnsResLameDelegationName.name: dnsResLameDelegationName
dnsResLameDelegationName.description: DNS name for which lame delegation was received.

dnsResLameDelegationClass.name: dnsResLameDelegationClass
dnsResLameDelegationClass.description: DNS class of received lame delegation.

dnsResLameDelegationCounts.name: dnsResLameDelegationCounts
dnsResLameDelegationCounts.description: How many times this lame delegation has been received.

dnsResLameDelegationStatus.name: dnsResLameDelegationStatus
dnsResLameDelegationStatus.description: Status column for the lame delegation table. Since only the agent (DNS resolver) creates rows in this table, the only values that a manager may write to this variable are active(1) and destroy(6).

dnsResCacheStatus.name: dnsResCacheStatus
dnsResCacheStatus.description: Status/action for the resolver's cache. enabled(1) means that the use of the cache is allowed. Query operations can return this state. disabled(2) means that the cache is not being used. Query operations can return this state. Setting this variable to clear(3) deletes the entire contents of the resolver's cache, but does not otherwise change the resolver's state. The status will retain its previous value from before the clear operation (i.e., enabled(1) or disabled(2)). The value of clear(3) can NOT be returned by a query operation.

dnsResCacheMaxTTL.name: dnsResCacheMaxTTL
dnsResCacheMaxTTL.description: Maximum Time-To-Live for RRs in this cache. If the resolver does not implement a TTL ceiling, the value of this field should be zero.

dnsResCacheGoodCaches.name: dnsResCacheGoodCaches
dnsResCacheGoodCaches.description: Number of RRs the resolver has cached successfully.

dnsResCacheBadCaches.name: dnsResCacheBadCaches
dnsResCacheBadCaches.description: Number of RRs the resolver has refused to cache because they appear to be dangerous or irrelevant. E.g., RRs with suspiciously high TTLs, unsolicited root information, or that just don't appear to be relevant to the question the resolver asked.

dnsResCacheRRTable.name: dnsResCacheRRTable
dnsResCacheRRTable.description: This table contains information about all the resource records currently in the resolver's cache.

dnsResCacheRREntry.name: dnsResCacheRREntry
dnsResCacheRREntry.description: An entry in the resolvers's cache. Rows may be created only by the resolver. SNMP SET requests may be used to delete rows.

dnsResCacheRRName.name: dnsResCacheRRName
dnsResCacheRRName.description: Owner name of the Resource Record in the cache which is identified in this row of the table. As described in RFC-1034, the owner of the record is the domain name were the RR is found.

dnsResCacheRRClass.name: dnsResCacheRRClass
dnsResCacheRRClass.description: DNS class of the Resource Record in the cache which is identified in this row of the table.

dnsResCacheRRType.name: dnsResCacheRRType
dnsResCacheRRType.description: DNS type of the Resource Record in the cache which is identified in this row of the table.

dnsResCacheRRTTL.name: dnsResCacheRRTTL
dnsResCacheRRTTL.description: Time-To-Live of RR in DNS cache. This is the initial TTL value which was received with the RR when it was originally received.

dnsResCacheRRElapsedTTL.name: dnsResCacheRRElapsedTTL
dnsResCacheRRElapsedTTL.description: Elapsed seconds since RR was received.

dnsResCacheRRSource.name: dnsResCacheRRSource
dnsResCacheRRSource.description: Host from which RR was received, 0.0.0.0 if unknown.

dnsResCacheRRData.name: dnsResCacheRRData
dnsResCacheRRData.description: RDATA portion of a cached RR. The value is in the format defined for the particular DNS class and type of the resource record.

dnsResCacheRRStatus.name: dnsResCacheRRStatus
dnsResCacheRRStatus.description: Status column for the resolver cache table. Since only the agent (DNS resolver) creates rows in this table, the only values that a manager may write to this variable are active(1) and destroy(6).

dnsResCacheRRIndex.name: dnsResCacheRRIndex
dnsResCacheRRIndex.description: A value which makes entries in the table unique when the other index values (dnsResCacheRRName, dnsResCacheRRClass, and dnsResCacheRRType) do not provide a unique index.

dnsResCacheRRPrettyName.name: dnsResCacheRRPrettyName
dnsResCacheRRPrettyName.description: Name of the RR at this row in the table. This is identical to the dnsResCacheRRName variable, except that character case is preserved in this variable, per DNS conventions.

dnsResNCacheStatus.name: dnsResNCacheStatus
dnsResNCacheStatus.description: Status/action for the resolver's negative response cache. enabled(1) means that the use of the negative response cache is allowed. Query operations can return this state. disabled(2) means that the negative response cache is not being used. Query operations can return this state. Setting this variable to clear(3) deletes the entire contents of the resolver's negative response cache. The status will retain its previous value from before the clear operation (i.e., enabled(1) or disabled(2)). The value of clear(3) can NOT be returned by a query operation.

dnsResNCacheMaxTTL.name: dnsResNCacheMaxTTL
dnsResNCacheMaxTTL.description: Maximum Time-To-Live for cached authoritative errors. If the resolver does not implement a TTL ceiling, the value of this field should be zero.

dnsResNCacheGoodNCaches.name: dnsResNCacheGoodNCaches
dnsResNCacheGoodNCaches.description: Number of authoritative errors the resolver has cached successfully.

dnsResNCacheBadNCaches.name: dnsResNCacheBadNCaches
dnsResNCacheBadNCaches.description: Number of authoritative errors the resolver would have liked to cache but was unable to because the appropriate SOA RR was not supplied or looked suspicious.

dnsResNCacheErrTable.name: dnsResNCacheErrTable
dnsResNCacheErrTable.description: The resolver's negative response cache. This table contains information about authoritative errors that have been cached by the resolver.

dnsResNCacheErrEntry.name: dnsResNCacheErrEntry
dnsResNCacheErrEntry.description: An entry in the resolver's negative response cache table. Only the resolver can create rows. SNMP SET requests may be used to delete rows.

dnsResNCacheErrQName.name: dnsResNCacheErrQName
dnsResNCacheErrQName.description: QNAME associated with a cached authoritative error.

dnsResNCacheErrQClass.name: dnsResNCacheErrQClass
dnsResNCacheErrQClass.description: DNS QCLASS associated with a cached authoritative error.

dnsResNCacheErrQType.name: dnsResNCacheErrQType
dnsResNCacheErrQType.description: DNS QTYPE associated with a cached authoritative error.

dnsResNCacheErrTTL.name: dnsResNCacheErrTTL
dnsResNCacheErrTTL.description: Time-To-Live of a cached authoritative error at the time of the error, it should not be decremented by the number of seconds since it was received. This should be the TTL as copied from the MINIMUM field of the SOA that accompanied the authoritative error, or a smaller value if the resolver implements a ceiling on negative response cache TTLs.

dnsResNCacheErrElapsedTTL.name: dnsResNCacheErrElapsedTTL
dnsResNCacheErrElapsedTTL.description: Elapsed seconds since authoritative error was received.

dnsResNCacheErrSource.name: dnsResNCacheErrSource
dnsResNCacheErrSource.description: Host which sent the authoritative error, 0.0.0.0 if unknown.

dnsResNCacheErrCode.name: dnsResNCacheErrCode
dnsResNCacheErrCode.description: The authoritative error that has been cached: nonexistantName(1) indicates an authoritative name error (RCODE = 3). noData(2) indicates an authoritative response with no error (RCODE = 0) and no relevant data. other(3) indicates some other cached authoritative error. At present, no such errors are known to exist.

dnsResNCacheErrStatus.name: dnsResNCacheErrStatus
dnsResNCacheErrStatus.description: Status column for the resolver negative response cache table. Since only the agent (DNS resolver) creates rows in this table, the only values that a manager may write to this variable are active(1) and destroy(6).

dnsResNCacheErrIndex.name: dnsResNCacheErrIndex
dnsResNCacheErrIndex.description: A value which makes entries in the table unique when the other index values (dnsResNCacheErrQName, dnsResNCacheErrQClass, and dnsResNCacheErrQType) do not provide a unique index.

dnsResNCacheErrPrettyName.name: dnsResNCacheErrPrettyName
dnsResNCacheErrPrettyName.description: QNAME associated with this row in the table. This is identical to the dnsResNCacheErrQName variable, except that character case is preserved in this variable, per DNS conventions.

dnsResOptCounterReferals.name: dnsResOptCounterReferals
dnsResOptCounterReferals.description: Number of responses which were received from servers redirecting query to another server.

dnsResOptCounterRetrans.name: dnsResOptCounterRetrans
dnsResOptCounterRetrans.description: Number requests retransmitted for all reasons.

dnsResOptCounterNoResponses.name: dnsResOptCounterNoResponses
dnsResOptCounterNoResponses.description: Number of queries that were retransmitted because of no response.

dnsResOptCounterRootRetrans.name: dnsResOptCounterRootRetrans
dnsResOptCounterRootRetrans.description: Number of queries that were retransmitted that were to root servers.

dnsResOptCounterInternals.name: dnsResOptCounterInternals
dnsResOptCounterInternals.description: Number of requests internally generated by the resolver.

dnsResOptCounterInternalTimeOuts.name: dnsResOptCounterInternalTimeOuts
dnsResOptCounterInternalTimeOuts.description: Number of requests internally generated which timed out.

dnsResConfigGroup.name: dnsResConfigGroup
dnsResConfigGroup.description: A collection of objects providing basic configuration information for a DNS resolver implementation.

dnsResCounterGroup.name: dnsResCounterGroup
dnsResCounterGroup.description: A collection of objects providing basic instrumentation of a DNS resolver implementation.

dnsResLameDelegationGroup.name: dnsResLameDelegationGroup
dnsResLameDelegationGroup.description: A collection of objects providing instrumentation of `lame delegation' failures.

dnsResCacheGroup.name: dnsResCacheGroup
dnsResCacheGroup.description: A collection of objects providing access to and control of a DNS resolver's cache.

dnsResNCacheGroup.name: dnsResNCacheGroup
dnsResNCacheGroup.description: A collection of objects providing access to and control of a DNS resolver's negative response cache.

dnsResOptCounterGroup.name: dnsResOptCounterGroup
dnsResOptCounterGroup.description: A collection of objects providing further instrumentation applicable to many but not all DNS resolvers.

dnsResMIBCompliance.name: dnsResMIBCompliance
dnsResMIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for agents implementing the DNS resolver MIB extensions.
